&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Internal tool development.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;You leverage&amp;nbsp;agentic software development to&amp;nbsp;build the lightweight, functional tools the business needs — using no-code/low-code platforms, and scripting where it fits. You know which problems deserve which approach.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Operational efficiency.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;You take on a backlog of known inefficiencies and ship fixes. You move fast, you close tickets, and what you build holds up.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sustained tool adoption.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Anyone can launch a tool. The job is making sure it&#39;s still actively used 90 days after rollout — and that the team is getting more value from it over time, not less.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-functional translation.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;You sit between Operations, Sales, Customer Success, and Engineering. You translate operational pain into buildable solutions and technical constraints back into business terms.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
